Capital Expenditure (CapEx) involves upfront infrastructure investment, while Operational Expenditure (OpEx) focuses on pay-as-you-go consumption.

Traditional IT:

* Servers
* Datacenters
* Hardware purchases

Cloud:

* Subscription-based
* Elastic consumption

For example, startups benefit from OpEx by avoiding large infrastructure costs.

A real-life use case is scaling businesses.

Another example is enterprises optimizing financial flexibility.

This shift is a core cloud computing advantage.
